Package gov.usgs.anss.picker

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    FP6Instrumentation
    This interface allows instrumentation of the internals of the FilterPicker6 code.
    PickerCallback
    This is the interface that the CWBPicker (or any later supplier of data to a picker) uses.
    PickerInterface
    All pickers need to implement this class.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CWBCorrelationPicker  
    CWBFilterPicker6
    This is the USGS implementation of the FilterPicker6 using the CWBPicker parent class.
    CWBPicker
    This class provides the common data access and pick reporting from the NEIC CWB program QueryMom.
    CWBSubspaceDetector
    This class interfaces to the SubspaceDectector project using the CWBPicker conventions and infrastructure.
    CWBSubspaceManager
    This EdgeThreads looks at the Subspace Areas that are configured, computes whether any of the channels in the subspace are on this node (actually all of them should be on this node!), and configures the CWBSubspaceDetector.
    FP6InstrumentationDCK
    This is a sample instrumentation class DCK wrote which prints out picks in more detail and creates full time series of the characteristic function values.
    JsonDetectionSender
    This class implements various ways a JSON message can be configuration to be Sent out.
    MaintainDB
    This class insures that a DBConnectionThread to a given property name is constantly maintained with the DBConnectionThread name set to the property name.
    PickerManager
    This EdgeThreads looks at the QuerySpans available and if that seedname is configured for a picker, it starts up a picker and monitors it for running or changes in configuration.
